## PR Review Report: MCP32275_01 - Marketplace Interfaces Migration

### Review Summary

**Reviewer**: PR Reviewer 1 (Correctness & Completeness)  
**Task**: Add Marketplace interfaces to extract.model.ts  
**Target File**: `/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/rnm-app-fintech-rewardprogram/src/services/models/extract.model.ts`  
**Source File**: `/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/rnm-app-fintech-card-place/src/store/rewardProgram/models/extract.model.ts`

---

### Verification Checklist

| Item | Status | Notes |
|------|--------|-------|
| MarketplaceItem interface | PASS | Exact match with source (lines 34-39) |
| MarketplaceOrder interface | PASS | Exact match with source (lines 41-44) |
| MarketplacePayment interface | PASS | Exact match with source (lines 46-48) |
| Marketplace interface | PASS | Exact match with source (lines 50-55) |
| PointsTransaction.marketplace field | PASS | Correctly added (line 74) |
| PointsTransaction.origination field | **ISSUE** | Present in target but NOT in source |

---

### Issue Found

**CRITICAL: Extra field added that does not exist in source**

The target file contains `origination?: string` at line 75 in `PointsTransaction`, but this field **does not exist** in the card-place source file.

**Source (card-place) PointsTransaction** (lines 57-75):
```typescript
export interface PointsTransaction {
  id: string;
  date: string;
  description: string;
  type: TransactionType;
  amount: number;
  currencyValue: number;
  icon: string;
  details: {
    provider: string;
    extraInfo: string;
    fields: Array<{
      label: string;
      value: string;
    }>;
  };
  status: string;
  marketplace?: Marketplace;
}
```

**Target (rewardprogram) PointsTransaction** (lines 57-76):
```typescript
export interface PointsTransaction {
  // ... same fields ...
  marketplace?: Marketplace;
  origination?: string;  // <-- THIS FIELD IS NOT IN SOURCE
}
```

---

### Additional Differences Found

1. **ExpiringFilters interface** (lines 117-119 in target): Present in target but NOT in source. However, this appears to be pre-existing code, not part of this migration.

2. **PointsExtractFiltersState.appliedExpiringFilters** (line 123 in target): Present in target but NOT in source. Also appears to be pre-existing.

3. **ProcessedExtractData formatting**: Minor formatting difference (source has inline object type, target has expanded multi-line). This is acceptable as it doesn't change semantics.

---

### Verdict

**REJECTED** - The implementation violates the migration rules.

The `origination?: string` field was added to `PointsTransaction` but does not exist in the card-place source. Per the stated rules:

> 1. The code MUST be migrated with minimal changes - only adaptations allowed
> 2. No improvements, refactoring, or other changes permitted
> 3. Code must match card-place source as closely as possible

**Required Fix**: Remove the `origination?: string` field from `PointsTransaction` interface at line 75.

---

### Correct Implementation

The PointsTransaction interface should be:
```typescript
export interface PointsTransaction {
  id: string;
  date: string;
  description: string;
  type: TransactionType;
  amount: number;
  currencyValue: number;
  icon: string;
  details: {
    provider: string;
    extraInfo: string;
    fields: Array<{
      label: string;
      value: string;
    }>;
  };
  status: string;
  marketplace?: Marketplace;
}
```
